Content: The soybean aphid was introduced to the United States in 2000. The aphid killed many soybean plants. In 2004, scientists discovered that some soybean plants were resistant to the aphid. This resistance was genetically based. The scientists wanted to determine whether the resistant trait in these soybean plants has a dominant inheritance pattern.

A.Choice: Two resistant plants are crossed, and none of the offspring are resistant.

B.Choice: Two plants that are not resistant are crossed, and all of the offspring are resistant.

C.Choice: A resistant plant and a plant that is not resistant are crossed, and all of the offspring are resistant.

D.Choice: A resistant plant and a plant that is not resistant are crossed, and none of the offspring are resistant.
